cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.MM 

This paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for detecting people attributes in surveillance contexts. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a deep architecture that involves the use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs), which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with issues of poor resolution and occlusion, which could fall under the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper deals with surveillance footage, which could fall under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
